this flexibility gives it the means to designate bona fide credible private institutions as eligible institutions . 
there is no intent in this legislation to exclude such institutions . 
i go on to the Reform motion that would require the foundation to establish an appeal process for applicants who do not receive scholarships . 
we have to understand this is an arm ' s length foundation . 
it is completely within its purview , and the legislation allows for this flexibility , to establish an appeals process . 
establishing an appeals process pursuant to regulations established by the government would undermine the arm ' s length nature of the foundation . 
we cannot have it both ways . 
